    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Chronicles",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 18,
        "summary": "David subdues all the adversaries of Israel and reigns in justice over the people.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Now after this it came to pass, that David smote the Philistines, and subdued them, and took Gath and her towns out of the hand of the Philistines.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 8:1 (1\u201318).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 17:4.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he smote Moab; and the Moabites became David's servants, and brought gifts.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And David smote Hadarezer king of Zobah unto Hamath, as he went to stablish his dominion by the river Euphrates.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And David took from him a thousand chariots, and seven thousand horsemen, and twenty thousand footmen: David also houghed all the chariot horses, but reserved of them an hundred chariots.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And when the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadarezer king of Zobah, David slew of the Syrians two and twenty thousand men.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then David put garrisons in Syria-damascus; and the Syrians became David's servants, and brought gifts. Thus the Lord preserved David whithersoever he went.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And David took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadarezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Likewise from Tibhath, and from Chun, cities of Hadarezer, brought David very much brass, wherewith Solomon made the brasen sea, and the pillars, and the vessels of brass.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 5:16.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 7:23; 2\u00a0Chr. 4:15 (12\u201316).",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now when Tou king of Hamath heard how David had smitten all the host of Hadarezer king of Zobah;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He sent Hadoram his son to king David, to inquire of his welfare, and to congratulate him, because he had fought against Hadarezer, and smitten him; (for Hadarezer had war with Tou;) and with him all manner of vessels of gold and silver and brass.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 195
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Them also king David dedicated unto the Lord, with the silver and the gold that he brought from all these nations; from Edom, and from Moab, and from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines, and from Amalek.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover Abishai the son of Zeruiah slew of the Edomites in the valley of salt eighteen thousand.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he put garrisons in Edom; and all the Edomites became David's servants. Thus the Lord preserved David whithersoever he went.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 11:15.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So David reigned over all Israel, and executed judgment and justice among all his people.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the host; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud, recorder.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Zadok the son of Ahitub, and Abimelech the son of Abiathar, were the priests; and Shavsha was scribe;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and the sons of David were chief about the king.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}